==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /ˈɪntəˌnɛt/, /<tt>"Int@%nEt</tt>/
*(''US''): ĭnʹtərnĕt', /ˈɪntɚˌnɛt/, /<tt>Int3`nEt</tt>/

===Proper noun===
'''the Internet'''

#The specific [[internet]] consisting of the global [[network]] of [[computer]]s.

====Forms and variants====
*[[internet]] (''see'' '''Usage notes''' ''below'')

====Usage notes====
*Many people in consider that '''Internet''' should be capitalised in the context of the global network, reserving '''internet''' with a lower-case ''i'' for any other set of computer networks connected by internetworking.

====Synonyms====
*[[cyberspace]]
*the [[information superhighway]]
*the [[Net]], the net
*the [[World Wide Web]] (''imprecisely'')
*the [[Web]] (''imprecisely'')

